  <Name>k__BackingField: Job
  fancyName: 
  nickname: job
  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 51ee3e37f5ded7941ab6216610f6fc67, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - title: Prologue
      content: "  There once was a man named Job who lived in the land of Uz. He
        was blameless\u2014a man of complete integrity. He feared God and stayed
        away from evil. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He had seven sons and three daughters. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He owned 7,000 sheep, 3,000 camels, 500 teams of oxen, and 500 female
        donkeys. He also had many servants. He was, in fact, the richest person in
        that entire area.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Job\u2019s sons would take turns preparing feasts in their homes,
        and they would also invite their three sisters to celebrate with them. "
      comments: []
    - title: "Job\u2019s First Test"
      content: "When these celebrations ended\u2014sometimes after several days\u2014Job
        would purify his children. He would get up early in the morning and offer
        a burnt offering for each of them. For Job said to himself, \u201CPerhaps
        my children have sinned and have cursed God in their hearts.\u201D This was
        Job\u2019s regular practice.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'One day the members of the heavenly court[[COMMENT(0)]] came to present
        themselves before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, and the Accuser, Satan,[[COMMENT(1)]]
        came with them. '
      comments:
      - number: '1:6a '
        content: Hebrew <b>the sons of God.</b>
      - number: '1:6b '
        content: Hebrew <b>and the satan; </b>similarly throughout this chapter.
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWhere have you come from?\u201D the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        asked Satan.Satan answered the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, \u201CI have
        been patrolling the earth, watching everything that\u2019s going on.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> asked Satan, \u201CHave you
        noticed my servant Job? He is the finest man in all the earth. He is blameless\u2014a
        man of complete integrity. He fears God and stays away from evil.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Satan replied to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, \u201CYes, but
        Job has good reason to fear God. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You have always put a wall of protection around him and his home
        and his property. You have made him prosper in everything he does. Look how
        rich he is! '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But reach out and take away everything he has, and he will surely
        curse you to your face!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CAll right, you may test him,\u201D the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        said to Satan. \u201CDo whatever you want with everything he possesses, but
        don\u2019t harm him physically.\u201D So Satan left the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        presence.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "One day when Job\u2019s sons and daughters were feasting at the oldest
        brother\u2019s house, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "a messenger arrived at Job\u2019s home with this news: \u201CYour
        oxen were plowing, with the donkeys feeding beside them, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "when the Sabeans raided us. They stole all the animals and killed
        all the farmhands. I am the only one who escaped to tell you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "While he was still speaking, another messenger arrived with this
        news: \u201CThe fire of God has fallen from heaven and burned up your sheep
        and all the shepherds. I am the only one who escaped to tell you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "While he was still speaking, a third messenger arrived with this
        news: \u201CThree bands of Chaldean raiders have stolen your camels and killed
        your servants. I am the only one who escaped to tell you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "While he was still speaking, another messenger arrived with this
        news: \u201CYour sons and daughters were feasting in their oldest brother\u2019s
        home. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Suddenly, a powerful wind swept in from the wilderness and hit the
        house on all sides. The house collapsed, and all your children are dead.
        I am the only one who escaped to tell you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Job stood up and tore his robe in grief. Then he shaved his head
        and fell to the ground to worship. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He said,\u201CI came naked from my mother\u2019s womb,and I will
        be naked when I leave.The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave me what I had,and
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has taken it away.Praise the name of the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>!\u201D  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "Job\u2019s Second Test"
      content: '  One day the members of the heavenly court[[COMMENT(0)]] came again
        to present themselves before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, and the Accuser,
        Satan,[[COMMENT(1)]] came with them. '
      comments:
      - number: '2:1a '
        content: Hebrew <b>the sons of God.</b>
      - number: '2:1b '
        content: Hebrew <b>and the satan; </b>similarly throughout this chapter.
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWhere have you come from?\u201D the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        asked Satan.Satan answered the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, \u201CI have
        been patrolling the earth, watching everything that\u2019s going on.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> asked Satan, \u201CHave you
        noticed my servant Job? He is the finest man in all the earth. He is blameless\u2014a
        man of complete integrity. He fears God and stays away from evil. And he
        has maintained his integrity, even though you urged me to harm him without
        cause.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Satan replied to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, \u201CSkin for
        skin! A man will give up everything he has to save his life. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But reach out and take away his health, and he will surely curse
        you to your face!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CAll right, do with him as you please,\u201D the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        said to Satan. \u201CBut spare his life.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So Satan left the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s presence, and
        he struck Job with terrible boils from head to foot.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Job scraped his skin with a piece of broken pottery as he sat among
        the ashes. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "His wife said to him, \u201CAre you still trying to maintain your
        integrity? Curse God and die.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: "Job\u2019s Three Friends Share His Anguish"
      content: "But Job replied, \u201CYou talk like a foolish woman. Should we accept
        only good things from the hand of God and never anything bad?\u201D So in
        all this, Job said nothing wrong.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When three of Job\u2019s friends heard of the tragedy he had suffered,
        they got together and traveled from their homes to comfort and console him.
        Their names were Eliphaz the Temanite, Bildad the Shuhite, and Zophar the
        Naamathite. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When they saw Job from a distance, they scarcely recognized him.
        Wailing loudly, they tore their robes and threw dust into the air over their
        heads to show their grief. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "Job\u2019s First Speech"
      content: '  At last Job spoke, and he cursed the day of his birth. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He said:  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CLet the day of my birth be erased,and the night I was conceived.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Let that day be turned to darkness.Let it be lost even to God on
        high,and let no light shine on it.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Let the darkness and utter gloom claim that day for its own.Let a
        black cloud overshadow it,and let the darkness terrify it.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Let that night be blotted off the calendar,never again to be counted
        among the days of the year,never again to appear among the months.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Let that night be childless.Let it have no joy.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Let those who are experts at cursing\u2014whose cursing could rouse
        Leviathan[[COMMENT(0)]]\u2014curse that day.  "
      comments:
      - number: '3:8 '
        content: The identification of Leviathan is disputed, ranging from an earthly
          creature to a mythical sea monster in ancient literature.
    - title: 
      content: 'Let its morning stars remain dark.Let it hope for light, but in vain;may
        it never see the morning light.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Curse that day for failing to shut my mother\u2019s womb,for letting
        me be born to see all this trouble.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWhy wasn\u2019t I born dead?Why didn\u2019t I die as I came
        from the womb?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Why was I laid on my mother\u2019s lap?Why did she nurse me at her
        breasts?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Had I died at birth, I would now be at peace.I would be asleep and
        at rest.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I would rest with the world\u2019s kings and prime ministers,whose
        great buildings now lie in ruins.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I would rest with princes, rich in gold,whose palaces were filled
        with silver.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Why wasn\u2019t I buried like a stillborn child,like a baby who never
        lives to see the light?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For in death the wicked cause no trouble,and the weary are at rest.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Even captives are at ease in death,with no guards to curse them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Rich and poor are both there,and the slave is free from his master.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201COh, why give light to those in misery,and life to those who
        are bitter?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They long for death, and it won\u2019t come.They search for death
        more eagerly than for hidden treasure.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They\u2019re filled with joy when they finally die,and rejoice when
        they find the grave.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Why is life given to those with no future,those God has surrounded
        with difficulties?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I cannot eat for sighing;my groans pour out like water.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'What I always feared has happened to me.What I dreaded has come true.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "Eliphaz\u2019s First Response to Job"
      content: '  Then Eliphaz the Temanite replied to Job:  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWill you be patient and let me say a word?For who could keep
        from speaking out?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CIn the past you have encouraged many people;you have strengthened
        those who were weak.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Your words have supported those who were falling;you encouraged those
        with shaky knees.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But now when trouble strikes, you lose heart.You are terrified when
        it touches you.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Doesn\u2019t your reverence for God give you confidence?Doesn\u2019t
        your life of integrity give you hope?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CStop and think! Do the innocent die?When have the upright been
        destroyed?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'My experience shows that those who plant troubleand cultivate evil
        will harvest the same.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'A breath from God destroys them.They vanish in a blast of his anger.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The lion roars and the wildcat snarls,but the teeth of strong lions
        will be broken.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The fierce lion will starve for lack of prey,and the cubs of the
        lioness will be scattered.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThis truth was given to me in secret,as though whispered in
        my ear.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'It came to me in a disturbing vision at night,when people are in
        a deep sleep.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Fear gripped me,and my bones trembled.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'A spirit[[COMMENT(0)]] swept past my face,and my hair stood on end.[[COMMENT(1)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '4:15a '
        content: Or <b>wind; </b>also in 4:16.
      - number: '4:15b '
        content: Or <b>its wind sent shivers up my spine.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "The spirit stopped, but I couldn\u2019t see its shape.There was a
        form before my eyes.In the silence I heard a voice say,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u2018Can a mortal be innocent before God?Can anyone be pure before
        the Creator?\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CIf God does not trust his own angelsand has charged his messengers
        with foolishness,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'how much less will he trust people made of clay!They are made of
        dust, crushed as easily as a moth.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They are alive in the morning but dead by evening,gone forever without
        a trace.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "Eliphaz\u2019s Response Continues"
      content: "  \u201CCry for help, but will anyone answer you?Which of the angels[[COMMENT(0)]]
        will help you?  "
      comments:
      - number: '5:1 '
        content: Hebrew <b>the holy ones.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Surely resentment destroys the fool,and jealousy kills the simple.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I have seen that fools may be successful for the moment,but then
        comes sudden disaster.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Their children are abandoned far from help;they are crushed in court
        with no one to defend them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The hungry devour their harvest,even when it is guarded by brambles.[[COMMENT(0)]]The
        thirsty pant after their wealth.[[COMMENT(1)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '5:5a '
        content: The meaning of the Hebrew for this phrase is uncertain.
      - number: '5:5b '
        content: As in Greek and Syriac versions; Hebrew reads <b>A snare snatches
          their wealth.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'But evil does not spring from the soil,and trouble does not sprout
        from the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'People are born for troubleas readily as sparks fly up from a fire.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CIf I were you, I would go to Godand present my case to him.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He does great things too marvelous to understand.He performs countless
        miracles.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He gives rain for the earthand water for the fields.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He gives prosperity to the poorand protects those who suffer.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He frustrates the plans of schemersso the work of their hands will
        not succeed.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He traps the wise in their own clevernessso their cunning schemes
        are thwarted.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They find it is dark in the daytime,and they grope at noon as if
        it were night.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He rescues the poor from the cutting words of the strong,and rescues
        them from the clutches of the powerful.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And so at last the poor have hope,and the snapping jaws of the wicked
        are shut.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut consider the joy of those corrected by God!Do not despise
        the discipline of the Almighty when you sin.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For though he wounds, he also bandages.He strikes, but his hands
        also heal.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'From six disasters he will rescue you;even in the seventh, he will
        keep you from evil.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He will save you from death in time of famine,from the power of the
        sword in time of war.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You will be safe from slanderand have no fear when destruction comes.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You will laugh at destruction and famine;wild animals will not terrify
        you.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You will be at peace with the stones of the field,and its wild animals
        will be at peace with you.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You will know that your home is safe.When you survey your possessions,
        nothing will be missing.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You will have many children;your descendants will be as plentiful
        as grass!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You will go to the grave at a ripe old age,like a sheaf of grain
        harvested at the proper time!  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "Job\u2019s Second Speech: A Response to Eliphaz"
      content: '  Then Job spoke again:  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CIf my misery could be weighedand my troubles be put on the
        scales,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'they would outweigh all the sands of the sea.That is why I spoke
        impulsively.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For the Almighty has struck me down with his arrows.Their poison
        infects my spirit.God\u2019s terrors are lined up against me.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t I have a right to complain?Don\u2019t wild donkeys bray
        when they find no grass,and oxen bellow when they have no food?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t people complain about unsalted food?Does anyone want the
        tasteless white of an egg?[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '6:6 '
        content: Or <b>the tasteless juice of the mallow plant?</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'My appetite disappears when I look at it;I gag at the thought of
        eating it!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201COh, that I might have my request,that God would grant my desire.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I wish he would crush me.I wish he would reach out his hand and kill
        me.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'At least I can take comfort in this:Despite the pain,I have not denied
        the words of the Holy One.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But I don\u2019t have the strength to endure.I have nothing to live
        for.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Do I have the strength of a stone?Is my body made of bronze?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'No, I am utterly helpless,without any chance of success.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201COne should be kind to a fainting friend,but you accuse me without
        any fear of the Almighty.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '6:14 '
        content: Or <b>friend, / or he might lose his fear of the Almighty.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'My brothers, you have proved as unreliable as a seasonal brookthat
        overflows its banks in the spring  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'when it is swollen with ice and melting snow.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But when the hot weather arrives, the water disappears.The brook
        vanishes in the heat.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The caravans turn aside to be refreshed,but there is nothing to drink,
        so they die.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The caravans from Tema search for this water;the travelers from Sheba
        hope to find it.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They count on it but are disappointed.When they arrive, their hopes
        are dashed.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You, too, have given no help.You have seen my calamity, and you are
        afraid.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But why? Have I ever asked you for a gift?Have I begged for anything
        of yours for myself?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Have I asked you to rescue me from my enemies,or to save me from
        ruthless people?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Teach me, and I will keep quiet.Show me what I have done wrong.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Honest words can be painful,but what do your criticisms amount to?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Do you think your words are convincingwhen you disregard my cry of
        desperation?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You would even send an orphan into slavery[[COMMENT(0)]]or sell a
        friend.  '
      comments:
      - number: '6:27 '
        content: Hebrew <b>even gamble over an orphan.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Look at me!Would I lie to your face?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Stop assuming my guilt,for I have done no wrong.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CIs not all human life a struggle?Our lives are like that
        of a hired hand,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'like a worker who longs for the shade,like a servant waiting to be
        paid.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I, too, have been assigned months of futility,long and weary nights
        of misery.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Lying in bed, I think, \u2018When will it be morning?\u2019But the
        night drags on, and I toss till dawn.  "
      comments: []
    - title: Job Cries Out to God
      content: 'My body is covered with maggots and scabs.My skin breaks open, oozing
        with pus.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CMy days fly faster than a weaver\u2019s shuttle.They end without
        hope.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'O God, remember that my life is but a breath,and I will never again
        feel happiness.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You see me now, but not for long.You will look for me, but I will
        be gone.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Just as a cloud dissipates and vanishes,those who die[[COMMENT(0)]]
        will not come back.  '
      comments:
      - number: '7:9 '
        content: Hebrew <b>who go down to Sheol.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "They are gone forever from their home\u2014never to be seen again.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI cannot keep from speaking.I must express my anguish.My bitter
        soul must complain.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Am I a sea monster or a dragonthat you must place me under guard?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I think, \u2018My bed will comfort me,and sleep will ease my misery,\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'but then you shatter me with dreamsand terrify me with visions.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I would rather be strangled\u2014rather die than suffer like this.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I hate my life and don\u2019t want to go on living.Oh, leave me alone
        for my few remaining days.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWhat are people, that you should make so much of us,that you
        should think of us so often?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For you examine us every morningand test us every moment.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Why won\u2019t you leave me alone,at least long enough for me to
        swallow!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'If I have sinned, what have I done to you,O watcher of all humanity?Why
        make me your target?Am I a burden to you?[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '7:20 '
        content: As in Greek version; Hebrew reads <b>target, so that I am a burden
          to myself?</b>
  - verses:
    - title: "Bildad\u2019s First Response to Job"
      content: '  Then Bildad the Shuhite replied to Job:  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CHow long will you go on like this?You sound like a blustering
        wind.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Does God twist justice?Does the Almighty twist what is right?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Your children must have sinned against him,so their punishment was
        well deserved.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But if you pray to Godand seek the favor of the Almighty,  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'and if you are pure and live with integrity,he will surely rise up
        and restore your happy home.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And though you started with little,you will end with much.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CJust ask the previous generation.Pay attention to the experience
        of our ancestors.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For we were born but yesterday and know nothing.Our days on earth
        are as fleeting as a shadow.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But those who came before us will teach you.They will teach you the
        wisdom of old.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CCan papyrus reeds grow tall without a marsh?Can marsh grass
        flourish without water?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'While they are still flowering, not ready to be cut,they begin to
        wither more quickly than grass.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The same happens to all who forget God.The hopes of the godless evaporate.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Their confidence hangs by a thread.They are leaning on a spider\u2019s
        web.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They cling to their home for security, but it won\u2019t last.They
        try to hold it tight, but it will not endure.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The godless seem like a lush plant growing in the sunshine,its branches
        spreading across the garden.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Its roots grow down through a pile of stones;it takes hold on a bed
        of rocks.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But when it is uprooted,it\u2019s as though it never existed!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "That\u2019s the end of its life,and others spring up from the earth
        to replace it.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut look, God will not reject a person of integrity,nor will
        he lend a hand to the wicked.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He will once again fill your mouth with laughterand your lips with
        shouts of joy.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "Job\u2019s Third Speech: A Response to Bildad"
      content: '  Then Job spoke again:  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CYes, I know all this is true in principle.But how can a person
        be declared innocent in God\u2019s sight?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'If someone wanted to take God to court,[[COMMENT(0)]]would it be
        possible to answer him even once in a thousand times?  '
      comments:
      - number: '9:3 '
        content: Or <b>If God wanted to take someone to court.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'For God is so wise and so mighty.Who has ever challenged him successfully?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWithout warning, he moves the mountains,overturning them in
        his anger.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He shakes the earth from its place,and its foundations tremble.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "If he commands it, the sun won\u2019t riseand the stars won\u2019t
        shine.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He alone has spread out the heavensand marches on the waves of the
        sea.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He made all the stars\u2014the Bear and Orion,the Pleiades and the
        constellations of the southern sky.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He does great things too marvelous to understand.He performs countless
        miracles.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CYet when he comes near, I cannot see him.When he moves by,
        I do not see him go.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "If he snatches someone in death, who can stop him?Who dares to ask,
        \u2018What are you doing?\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And God does not restrain his anger.Even the monsters of the sea[[COMMENT(0)]]
        are crushed beneath his feet.  '
      comments:
      - number: '9:13 '
        content: Hebrew <b>the helpers of Rahab, </b>the name of a mythical sea monster
          that represents chaos in ancient literature.
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CSo who am I, that I should try to answer Godor even reason
        with him?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Even if I were right, I would have no defense.I could only plead
        for mercy.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And even if I summoned him and he responded,I\u2019m not sure he
        would listen to me.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For he attacks me with a stormand repeatedly wounds me without cause.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He will not let me catch my breath,but fills me instead with bitter
        sorrows.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "If it\u2019s a question of strength, he\u2019s the strong one.If
        it\u2019s a matter of justice, who dares to summon him[[COMMENT(0)]] to court?  "
      comments:
      - number: '9:19 '
        content: As in Greek version; Hebrew reads <b>me.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Though I am innocent, my own mouth would pronounce me guilty.Though
        I am blameless, it[[COMMENT(0)]] would prove me wicked.  '
      comments:
      - number: '9:20 '
        content: Or <b>he.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI am innocent,but it makes no difference to me\u2014I despise
        my life.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Innocent or wicked, it is all the same to God.That\u2019s why I say,
        \u2018He destroys both the blameless and the wicked.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When a plague[[COMMENT(0)]] sweeps through,he laughs at the death
        of the innocent.  '
      comments:
      - number: '9:23 '
        content: Or <b>disaster.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "The whole earth is in the hands of the wicked,and God blinds the
        eyes of the judges.If he\u2019s not the one who does it, who is?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CMy life passes more swiftly than a runner.It flees away without
        a glimpse of happiness.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'It disappears like a swift papyrus boat,like an eagle swooping down
        on its prey.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'If I decided to forget my complaints,to put away my sad face and
        be cheerful,  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I would still dread all the pain,for I know you will not find me
        innocent, O God.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Whatever happens, I will be found guilty.So what\u2019s the use of
        trying?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Even if I were to wash myself with soapand clean my hands with lye,  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'you would plunge me into a muddy ditch,and my own filthy clothing
        would hate me.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CGod is not a mortal like me,so I cannot argue with him or take
        him to trial.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'If only there were a mediator between us,someone who could bring
        us together.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The mediator could make God stop beating me,and I would no longer
        live in terror of his punishment.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Job Frames His Plea to God
      content: "  \u201CI am disgusted with my life.Let me complain freely.My bitter
        soul must complain.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will say to God, \u2018Don\u2019t simply condemn me\u2014tell me
        the charge you are bringing against me.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'What do you gain by oppressing me?Why do you reject me, the work
        of your own hands,while smiling on the schemes of the wicked?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Are your eyes like those of a human?Do you see things only as people
        see them?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Is your lifetime only as long as ours?Is your life so short  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'that you must quickly probe for my guiltand search for my sin?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Although you know I am not guilty,no one can rescue me from your
        hands.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201C\u2018You formed me with your hands; you made me,yet now you
        completely destroy me.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Remember that you made me from dust\u2014will you turn me back to
        dust so soon?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You guided my conceptionand formed me in the womb.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '10:10 '
        content: Hebrew <b>You poured me out like milk / and curdled me like cheese.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'You clothed me with skin and flesh,and you knit my bones and sinews
        together.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You gave me life and showed me your unfailing love.My life was preserved
        by your care.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201C\u2018Yet your real motive\u2014your true intent\u2014  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'was to watch me, and if I sinned,you would not forgive my guilt.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "If I am guilty, too bad for me;and even if I\u2019m innocent, I can\u2019t
        hold my head high,because I am filled with shame and misery.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And if I hold my head high, you hunt me like a lionand display your
        awesome power against me.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Again and again you witness against me.You pour out your growing
        anger on meand bring fresh armies against me.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201C\u2018Why, then, did you deliver me from my mother\u2019s womb?Why
        didn\u2019t you let me die at birth?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'It would be as though I had never existed,going directly from the
        womb to the grave.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I have only a few days left, so leave me alone,that I may have a
        moment of comfort  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "before I leave\u2014never to return\u2014for the land of darkness
        and utter gloom.  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "Zophar\u2019s First Response to Job"
      content: '  Then Zophar the Naamathite replied to Job:  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CShouldn\u2019t someone answer this torrent of words?Is a person
        proved innocent just by a lot of talking?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Should I remain silent while you babble on?When you mock God, shouldn\u2019t
        someone make you ashamed?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You claim, \u2018My beliefs are pure,\u2019and \u2018I am clean in
        the sight of God.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'If only God would speak;if only he would tell you what he thinks!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'If only he would tell you the secrets of wisdom,for true wisdom is
        not a simple matter.Listen! God is doubtless punishing youfar less than you
        deserve!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CCan you solve the mysteries of God?Can you discover everything
        about the Almighty?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Such knowledge is higher than the heavens\u2014and who are you?It
        is deeper than the underworld[[COMMENT(0)]]\u2014what do you know?  "
      comments:
      - number: '11:8 '
        content: Hebrew <b>than Sheol.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'It is broader than the earthand wider than the sea.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'If God comes and puts a person in prisonor calls the court to order,
        who can stop him?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For he knows those who are false,and he takes note of all their sins.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "An empty-headed person won\u2019t become wiseany more than a wild
        donkey can bear a human child.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '11:12 '
        content: Or <b>than a wild male donkey can bear a tame colt.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CIf only you would prepare your heartand lift up your hands
        to him in prayer!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Get rid of your sins,and leave all iniquity behind you.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then your face will brighten with innocence.You will be strong and
        free of fear.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You will forget your misery;it will be like water flowing away.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Your life will be brighter than the noonday.Even darkness will be
        as bright as morning.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Having hope will give you courage.You will be protected and will
        rest in safety.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You will lie down unafraid,and many will look to you for help.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "Job\u2019s Fourth Speech: A Response to Zophar"
      content: '  Then Job spoke again:  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CYou people really know everything, don\u2019t you?And when
        you die, wisdom will die with you!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Well, I know a few things myself\u2014and you\u2019re no better than
        I am.Who doesn\u2019t know these things you\u2019ve been saying?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Yet my friends laugh at me,for I call on God and expect an answer.I
        am a just and blameless man,yet they laugh at me.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'People who are at ease mock those in trouble.They give a push to
        people who are stumbling.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But robbers are left in peace,and those who provoke God live in safety\u2014though
        God keeps them in his power.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '12:6 '
        content: "Or <b>safety\u2014those who try to manipulate God. </b>The meaning
          of the Hebrew is uncertain."
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CJust ask the animals, and they will teach you.Ask the birds
        of the sky, and they will tell you.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Speak to the earth, and it will instruct you.Let the fish in the
        sea speak to you.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For they all knowthat my disaster[[COMMENT(0)]] has come from the
        hand of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments:
      - number: '12:9 '
        content: Hebrew <b>that this.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'For the life of every living thing is in his hand,and the breath
        of every human being.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The ear tests the words it hearsjust as the mouth distinguishes between
        foods.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Wisdom belongs to the aged,and understanding to the old.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut true wisdom and power are found in God;counsel and understanding
        are his.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'What he destroys cannot be rebuilt.When he puts someone in prison,
        there is no escape.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'If he holds back the rain, the earth becomes a desert.If he releases
        the waters, they flood the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Yes, strength and wisdom are his;deceivers and deceived are both
        in his power.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He leads counselors away, stripped of good judgment;wise judges become
        fools.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He removes the royal robe of kings.They are led away with ropes around
        their waist.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He leads priests away, stripped of status;he overthrows those with
        long years in power.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He silences the trusted adviserand removes the insight of the elders.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He pours disgrace upon princesand disarms the strong.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CHe uncovers mysteries hidden in darkness;he brings light to
        the deepest gloom.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He builds up nations, and he destroys them.He expands nations, and
        he abandons them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He strips kings of understandingand leaves them wandering in a pathless
        wasteland.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Job Wants to Argue His Case with God
      content: "  \u201CLook, I have seen all this with my own eyesand heard it with
        my own ears, and now I understand.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I know as much as you do.You are no better than I am.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'As for me, I would speak directly to the Almighty.I want to argue
        my case with God himself.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'As for you, you smear me with lies.As physicians, you are worthless
        quacks.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "If only you could be silent!That\u2019s the wisest thing you could
        do.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Listen to my charge;pay attention to my arguments.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CAre you defending God with lies?Do you make your dishonest
        arguments for his sake?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Will you slant your testimony in his favor?Will you argue God\u2019s
        case for him?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'What will happen when he finds out what you are doing?Can you fool
        him as easily as you fool people?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'No, you will be in trouble with himif you secretly slant your testimony
        in his favor.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Doesn\u2019t his majesty terrify you?Doesn\u2019t your fear of him
        overwhelm you?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Your platitudes are as valuable as ashes.Your defense is as fragile
        as a clay pot.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBe silent now and leave me alone.Let me speak, and I will face
        the consequences.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Why should I put myself in mortal danger[[COMMENT(0)]]and take my
        life in my own hands?  '
      comments:
      - number: '13:14 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Why should I take my flesh in my teeth.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'God might kill me, but I have no other hope.[[COMMENT(0)]]I am going
        to argue my case with him.  '
      comments:
      - number: '13:15 '
        content: An alternate reading in the Masoretic Text reads <b>God might kill
          me, but I hope in him.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "But this is what will save me\u2014I am not godless.If I were, I
        could not stand before him.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CListen closely to what I am about to say.Hear me out.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I have prepared my case;I will be proved innocent.  '
      comments: []
    - title: Job Asks How He Has Sinned
      content: 'Who can argue with me over this?And if you prove me wrong, I will
        remain silent and die.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CO God, grant me these two things,and then I will be able to
        face you.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Remove your heavy hand from me,and don\u2019t terrify me with your
        awesome presence.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Now summon me, and I will answer!Or let me speak to you, and you
        reply.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Tell me, what have I done wrong?Show me my rebellion and my sin.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Why do you turn away from me?Why do you treat me as your enemy?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Would you terrify a leaf blown by the wind?Would you chase dry straw?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CYou write bitter accusations against meand bring up all the
        sins of my youth.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You put my feet in stocks.You examine all my paths.You trace all
        my footprints.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CHow frail is humanity!How short is life, how full of trouble!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'We blossom like a flower and then wither.Like a passing shadow, we
        quickly disappear.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Must you keep an eye on such a frail creatureand demand an accounting
        from me?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Who can bring purity out of an impure person?No one!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You have decided the length of our lives.You know how many months
        we will live,and we are not given a minute longer.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So leave us alone and let us rest!We are like hired hands, so let
        us finish our work in peace.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CEven a tree has more hope!If it is cut down, it will sprout
        againand grow new branches.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Though its roots have grown old in the earthand its stump decays,  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'at the scent of water it will budand sprout again like a new seedling.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut when people die, their strength is gone.They breathe their
        last, and then where are they?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'As water evaporates from a lakeand a river disappears in drought,  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'people are laid to rest and do not rise again.Until the heavens are
        no more, they will not wake upnor be roused from their sleep.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI wish you would hide me in the grave[[COMMENT(0)]]and forget
        me there until your anger has passed.But mark your calendar to think of me
        again!  "
      comments:
      - number: '14:13 '
        content: Hebrew <b>in Sheol.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Can the dead live again?If so, this would give me hope through all
        my years of struggle,and I would eagerly await the release of death.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You would call and I would answer,and you would yearn for me, your
        handiwork.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For then you would guard my steps,instead of watching for my sins.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'My sins would be sealed in a pouch,and you would cover my guilt.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut instead, as mountains fall and crumbleand as rocks fall
        from a cliff,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "as water wears away the stonesand floods wash away the soil,so you
        destroy people\u2019s hope.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You always overpower them, and they pass from the scene.You disfigure
        them in death and send them away.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They never know if their children grow up in honoror sink to insignificance.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "Eliphaz\u2019s Second Response to Job"
      content: '  Then Eliphaz the Temanite replied:  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CA wise man wouldn\u2019t answer with such empty talk!You are
        nothing but a windbag.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The wise don\u2019t engage in empty chatter.What good are such words?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Have you no fear of God,no reverence for him?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Your sins are telling your mouth what to say.Your words are based
        on clever deception.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Your own mouth condemns you, not I.Your own lips testify against
        you.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWere you the first person ever born?Were you born before the
        hills were made?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Were you listening at God\u2019s secret council?Do you have a monopoly
        on wisdom?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "What do you know that we don\u2019t?What do you understand that we
        do not?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'On our side are aged, gray-haired menmuch older than your father!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CIs God\u2019s comfort too little for you?Is his gentle word
        not enough?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'What has taken away your reason?What has weakened your vision,[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '15:12 '
        content: Or <b>Why do your eyes flash with anger; </b>Hebrew reads <b>Why
          do your eyes blink.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'that you turn against Godand say all these evil things?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Can any mortal be pure?Can anyone born of a woman be just?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Look, God does not even trust the angels.[[COMMENT(0)]]Even the heavens
        are not absolutely pure in his sight.  '
      comments:
      - number: '15:15 '
        content: Hebrew <b>the holy ones.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'How much less pure is a corrupt and sinful personwith a thirst for
        wickedness!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CIf you will listen, I will show you.I will answer you from
        my own experience.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And it is confirmed by the reports of wise menwho have heard the
        same thing from their fathers\u2014  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'from those to whom the land was givenlong before any foreigners arrived.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThe wicked writhe in pain throughout their lives.Years of trouble
        are stored up for the ruthless.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The sound of terror rings in their ears,and even on good days they
        fear the attack of the destroyer.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They dare not go out into the darknessfor fear they will be murdered.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They wander around, saying, \u2018Where can I find bread?\u2019[[COMMENT(0)]]They
        know their day of destruction is near.  "
      comments:
      - number: '15:23 '
        content: Greek version reads <b>He is appointed to be food for a vulture.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'That dark day terrifies them.They live in distress and anguish,like
        a king preparing for battle.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For they shake their fists at God,defying the Almighty.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Holding their strong shields,they defiantly charge against him.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThese wicked people are heavy and prosperous;their waists bulge
        with fat.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But their cities will be ruined.They will live in abandoned housesthat
        are ready to tumble down.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Their riches will not last,and their wealth will not endure.Their
        possessions will no longer spread across the horizon.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThey will not escape the darkness.The burning sun will wither
        their shoots,and the breath of God will destroy them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Let them no longer fool themselves by trusting in empty riches,for
        emptiness will be their only reward.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They will be cut down in the prime of life;their branches will never
        again be green.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They will be like a vine whose grapes are harvested too early,like
        an olive tree that loses its blossoms before the fruit can form.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For the godless are barren.Their homes, enriched through bribery,
        will burn.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "Job\u2019s Fifth Speech: A Response to Eliphaz"
      content: '  Then Job spoke again:  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI have heard all this before.What miserable comforters you
        are!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Won\u2019t you ever stop blowing hot air?What makes you keep on talking?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I could say the same things if you were in my place.I could spout
        off criticism and shake my head at you.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But if it were me, I would encourage you.I would try to take away
        your grief.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Instead, I suffer if I defend myself,and I suffer no less if I refuse
        to speak.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CO God, you have ground me downand devastated my family.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "As if to prove I have sinned, you\u2019ve reduced me to skin and
        bones.My gaunt flesh testifies against me.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'God hates me and angrily tears me apart.He snaps his teeth at meand
        pierces me with his eyes.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'People jeer and laugh at me.They slap my cheek in contempt.A mob
        gathers against me.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'God has handed me over to sinners.He has tossed me into the hands
        of the wicked.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI was living quietly until he shattered me.He took me by the
        neck and broke me in pieces.Then he set me up as his target,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'and now his archers surround me.His arrows pierce me without mercy.The
        ground is wet with my blood.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '16:13 '
        content: Hebrew <b>my gall.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Again and again he smashes against me,charging at me like a warrior.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I wear burlap to show my grief.My pride lies in the dust.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'My eyes are red with weeping;dark shadows circle my eyes.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Yet I have done no wrong,and my prayer is pure.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CO earth, do not conceal my blood.Let it cry out on my behalf.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Even now my witness is in heaven.My advocate is there on high.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'My friends scorn me,but I pour out my tears to God.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I need someone to mediate between God and me,as a person mediates
        between friends.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Job Continues to Defend His Innocence
      content: "  \u201CMy spirit is crushed,and my life is nearly snuffed out.The
        grave is ready to receive me.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I am surrounded by mockers.I watch how bitterly they taunt me.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CYou must defend my innocence, O God,since no one else will
        stand up for me.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You have closed their minds to understanding,but do not let them
        triumph.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They betray their friends for their own advantage,so let their children
        faint with hunger.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CGod has made a mockery of me among the people;they spit in
        my face.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'My eyes are swollen with weeping,and I am but a shadow of my former
        self.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The virtuous are horrified when they see me.The innocent rise up
        against the ungodly.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The righteous keep moving forward,and those with clean hands become
        stronger and stronger.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CAs for all of you, come back with a better argument,though
        I still won\u2019t find a wise man among you.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "My days are over.My hopes have disappeared.My heart\u2019s desires
        are broken.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'These men say that night is day;they claim that the darkness is light.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'What if I go to the grave[[COMMENT(0)]]and make my bed in darkness?  '
      comments:
      - number: '17:13 '
        content: Hebrew <b>to Sheol; </b>also in 17:16.
    - title: 
      content: 'What if I call the grave my father,and the maggot my mother or my
        sister?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Where then is my hope?Can anyone find it?  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "Bildad\u2019s Second Response to Job"
      content: '  Then Bildad the Shuhite replied:  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CHow long before you stop talking?Speak sense if you want us
        to answer!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Do you think we are mere animals?Do you think we are stupid?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You may tear out your hair in anger,but will that destroy the earth?Will
        it make the rocks tremble?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CSurely the light of the wicked will be snuffed out.The sparks
        of their fire will not glow.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The light in their tent will grow dark.The lamp hanging above them
        will be quenched.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The confident stride of the wicked will be shortened.Their own schemes
        will be their downfall.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The wicked walk into a net.They fall into a pit.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'A trap grabs them by the heel.A snare holds them tight.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'A noose lies hidden on the ground.A rope is stretched across their
        path.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CTerrors surround the wickedand trouble them at every step.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Hunger depletes their strength,and calamity waits for them to stumble.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Disease eats their skin;death devours their limbs.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They are torn from the security of their homesand are brought down
        to the king of terrors.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The homes of the wicked will burn down;burning sulfur rains on their
        houses.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Their roots will dry up,and their branches will wither.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'All memory of their existence will fade from the earth;no one will
        remember their names.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They will be thrust from light into darkness,driven from the world.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They will have neither children nor grandchildren,nor any survivor
        in the place where they lived.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'People in the west are appalled at their fate;people in the east
        are horrified.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "Job\u2019s Sixth Speech: A Response to Bildad"
      content: '  Then Job spoke again:  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CHow long will you torture me?How long will you try to crush
        me with your words?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You have already insulted me ten times.You should be ashamed of treating
        me so badly.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Even if I have sinned,that is my concern, not yours.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You think you\u2019re better than I am,using my humiliation as evidence
        of my sin.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But it is God who has wronged me,capturing me in his net.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '19:6 '
        content: Or <b>for I am like a city under siege.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI cry out, \u2018Help!\u2019 but no one answers me.I protest,
        but there is no justice.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'God has blocked my way so I cannot move.He has plunged my path into
        darkness.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He has stripped me of my honorand removed the crown from my head.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He has demolished me on every side, and I am finished.He has uprooted
        my hope like a fallen tree.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'His fury burns against me;he counts me as an enemy.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'His troops advance.They build up roads to attack me.They camp all
        around my tent.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CMy relatives stay far away,and my friends have turned against
        me.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'My family is gone,and my close friends have forgotten me.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'My servants and maids consider me a stranger.I am like a foreigner
        to them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When I call my servant, he doesn\u2019t come;I have to plead with
        him!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'My breath is repulsive to my wife.I am rejected by my own family.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Even young children despise me.When I stand to speak, they turn their
        backs on me.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'My close friends detest me.Those I loved have turned against me.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I have been reduced to skin and bonesand have escaped death by the
        skin of my teeth.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CHave mercy on me, my friends, have mercy,for the hand of God
        has struck me.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Must you also persecute me, like God does?Haven\u2019t you chewed
        me up enough?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201COh, that my words could be recorded.Oh, that they could be
        inscribed on a monument,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'carved with an iron chisel and filled with lead,engraved forever
        in the rock.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut as for me, I know that my Redeemer lives,and he will stand
        upon the earth at last.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And after my body has decayed,yet in my body I will see God![[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '19:26 '
        content: Or <b>without my body I will see God. </b>The meaning of the Hebrew
          is uncertain.
    - title: 
      content: 'I will see him for myself.Yes, I will see him with my own eyes.I
        am overwhelmed at the thought!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CHow dare you go on persecuting me,saying, \u2018It\u2019s his
        own fault\u2019?  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "Zophar\u2019s Second Response to Job"
      content: '  Then Zophar the Naamathite replied:  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI must replybecause I am greatly disturbed.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I\u2019ve had to endure your insults,but now my spirit prompts me
        to reply.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CDon\u2019t you realize that from the beginning of time,ever
        since people were first placed on the earth,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'the triumph of the wicked has been short livedand the joy of the
        godless has been only temporary?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Though the pride of the godless reaches to the heavensand their heads
        touch the clouds,  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "yet they will vanish forever,thrown away like their own dung.Those
        who knew them will ask,\u2018Where are they?\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They will fade like a dream and not be found.They will vanish like
        a vision in the night.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Those who once saw them will see them no more.Their families will
        never see them again.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Their children will beg from the poor,for they must give back their
        stolen riches.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Though they are young,their bones will lie in the dust.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThey enjoyed the sweet taste of wickedness,letting it melt
        under their tongue.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They savored it,holding it long in their mouths.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But suddenly the food in their bellies turns sour,a poisonous venom
        in their stomach.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They will vomit the wealth they swallowed.God won\u2019t let them
        keep it down.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They will suck the poison of cobras.The viper will kill them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They will never again enjoy streams of olive oilor rivers of milk
        and honey.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They will give back everything they worked for.Their wealth will
        bring them no joy.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For they oppressed the poor and left them destitute.They foreclosed
        on their homes.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They were always greedy and never satisfied.Nothing remains of all
        the things they dreamed about.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Nothing is left after they finish gorging themselves.Therefore, their
        prosperity will not endure.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CIn the midst of plenty, they will run into troubleand be overcome
        by misery.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'May God give them a bellyful of trouble.May God rain down his anger
        upon them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When they try to escape an iron weapon,a bronze-tipped arrow will
        pierce them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The arrow is pulled from their back,and the arrowhead glistens with
        blood.[[COMMENT(0)]]The terrors of death are upon them.  '
      comments:
      - number: '20:25 '
        content: Hebrew <b>with gall.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Their treasures will be thrown into deepest darkness.A wildfire will
        devour their goods,consuming all they have left.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The heavens will reveal their guilt,and the earth will testify against
        them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "A flood will sweep away their house.God\u2019s anger will descend
        on them in torrents.  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "Job\u2019s Seventh Speech: A Response to Zophar"
      content: '  Then Job spoke again:  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CListen closely to what I am saying.That\u2019s one consolation
        you can give me.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Bear with me, and let me speak.After I have spoken, you may resume
        mocking me.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CMy complaint is with God, not with people.I have good reason
        to be so impatient.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Look at me and be stunned.Put your hand over your mouth in shock.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When I think about what I am saying, I shudder.My body trembles.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWhy do the wicked prosper,growing old and powerful?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They live to see their children grow up and settle down,and they
        enjoy their grandchildren.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Their homes are safe from every fear,and God does not punish them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Their bulls never fail to breed.Their cows bear calves and never
        miscarry.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They let their children frisk about like lambs.Their little ones
        skip and dance.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They sing with tambourine and harp.They celebrate to the sound of
        the flute.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They spend their days in prosperity,then go down to the grave[[COMMENT(0)]]
        in peace.  '
      comments:
      - number: '21:13 '
        content: Hebrew <b>to Sheol.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "And yet they say to God, \u2018Go away.We want no part of you and
        your ways.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Who is the Almighty, and why should we obey him?What good will it
        do us to pray?\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: '(They think their prosperity is of their own doing,but I will have
        nothing to do with that kind of thinking.)  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CYet the light of the wicked never seems to be extinguished.Do
        they ever have trouble?Does God distribute sorrows to them in anger?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Are they driven before the wind like straw?Are they carried away
        by the storm like chaff?Not at all!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201C\u2018Well,\u2019 you say, \u2018at least God will punish their
        children!\u2019But I say he should punish the ones who sin,so that they understand
        his judgment.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Let them see their destruction with their own eyes.Let them drink
        deeply of the anger of the Almighty.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For they will not care what happens to their familyafter they are
        dead.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut who can teach a lesson to God,since he judges even the
        most powerful?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'One person dies in prosperity,completely comfortable and secure,  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'the picture of good health,vigorous and fit.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Another person dies in bitter poverty,never having tasted the good
        life.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But both are buried in the same dust,both eaten by the same maggots.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CLook, I know what you\u2019re thinking.I know the schemes you
        plot against me.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You will tell me of rich and wicked peoplewhose houses have vanished
        because of their sins.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But ask those who have been around,and they will tell you the truth.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Evil people are spared in times of calamityand are allowed to escape
        disaster.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'No one criticizes them openlyor pays them back for what they have
        done.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When they are carried to the grave,an honor guard keeps watch at
        their tomb.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'A great funeral procession goes to the cemetery.Many pay their respects
        as the body is laid to rest,and the earth gives sweet repose.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "Eliphaz\u2019s Third Response to Job"
      content: '  Then Eliphaz the Temanite replied:  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CCan a person do anything to help God?Can even a wise person
        be helpful to him?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Is it any advantage to the Almighty if you are righteous?Would it
        be any gain to him if you were perfect?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Is it because you\u2019re so pious that he accuses youand brings
        judgment against you?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "No, it\u2019s because of your wickedness!There\u2019s no limit to
        your sins.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CFor example, you must have lent money to your friendand demanded
        clothing as security.Yes, you stripped him to the bone.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You must have refused water for the thirstyand food for the hungry.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You probably think the land belongs to the powerfuland only the privileged
        have a right to it!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You must have sent widows away empty-handedand crushed the hopes
        of orphans.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'That is why you are surrounded by trapsand tremble from sudden fears.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'That is why you cannot see in the darkness,and waves of water cover
        you.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CGod is so great\u2014higher than the heavens,higher than the
        farthest stars.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But you reply, \u2018That\u2019s why God can\u2019t see what I am
        doing!How can he judge through the thick darkness?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For thick clouds swirl about him, and he cannot see us.He is way
        up there, walking on the vault of heaven.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWill you continue on the old pathswhere evil people have walked?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They were snatched away in the prime of life,the foundations of their
        lives washed away.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For they said to God, \u2018Leave us alone!What can the Almighty
        do to us?\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Yet he was the one who filled their homes with good things,so I will
        have nothing to do with that kind of thinking.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThe righteous will be happy to see the wicked destroyed,and
        the innocent will laugh in contempt.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They will say, \u2018See how our enemies have been destroyed.The
        last of them have been consumed in the fire.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CSubmit to God, and you will have peace;then things will go
        well for you.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Listen to his instructions,and store them in your heart.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "If you return to the Almighty, you will be restored\u2014so clean
        up your life.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'If you give up your lust for moneyand throw your precious gold into
        the river,  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'the Almighty himself will be your treasure.He will be your precious
        silver!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThen you will take delight in the Almightyand look up to God.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You will pray to him, and he will hear you,and you will fulfill your
        vows to him.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You will succeed in whatever you choose to do,and light will shine
        on the road ahead of you.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "If people are in trouble and you say, \u2018Help them,\u2019God will
        save them.  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "Job\u2019s Eighth Speech: A Response to Eliphaz"
      content: '  Then Job spoke again:  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CMy complaint today is still a bitter one,and I try hard not
        to groan aloud.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'If only I knew where to find God,I would go to his court.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I would lay out my caseand present my arguments.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then I would listen to his replyand understand what he says to me.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Would he use his great power to argue with me?No, he would give me
        a fair hearing.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Honest people can reason with him,so I would be forever acquitted
        by my judge.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I go east, but he is not there.I go west, but I cannot find him.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I do not see him in the north, for he is hidden.I look to the south,
        but he is concealed.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut he knows where I am going.And when he tests me, I will
        come out as pure as gold.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For I have stayed on God\u2019s paths;I have followed his ways and
        not turned aside.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I have not departed from his commands,but have treasured his words
        more than daily food.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But once he has made his decision, who can change his mind?Whatever
        he wants to do, he does.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So he will do to me whatever he has planned.He controls my destiny.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'No wonder I am so terrified in his presence.When I think of it, terror
        grips me.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'God has made me sick at heart;the Almighty has terrified me.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Job Asks Why the Wicked Are Not Punished
      content: "  \u201CWhy doesn\u2019t the Almighty bring the wicked to judgment?Why
        must the godly wait for him in vain?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Evil people steal land by moving the boundary markers.They steal
        livestock and put them in their own pastures.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They take the orphan\u2019s donkeyand demand the widow\u2019s ox
        as security for a loan.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The poor are pushed off the path;the needy must hide together for
        safety.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Like wild donkeys in the wilderness,the poor must spend all their
        time looking for food,searching even in the desert for food for their children.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They harvest a field they do not own,and they glean in the vineyards
        of the wicked.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'All night they lie naked in the cold,without clothing or covering.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They are soaked by mountain showers,and they huddle against the rocks
        for want of a home.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThe wicked snatch a widow\u2019s child from her breast,taking
        the baby as security for a loan.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The poor must go about naked, without any clothing.They harvest food
        for others while they themselves are starving.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They press out olive oil without being allowed to taste it,and they
        tread in the winepress as they suffer from thirst.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The groans of the dying rise from the city,and the wounded cry for
        help,yet God ignores their moaning.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWicked people rebel against the light.They refuse to acknowledge
        its waysor stay in its paths.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The murderer rises in the early dawnto kill the poor and needy;at
        night he is a thief.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The adulterer waits for the twilight,saying, \u2018No one will see
        me then.\u2019He hides his face so no one will know him.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Thieves break into houses at nightand sleep in the daytime.They are
        not acquainted with the light.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The black night is their morning.They ally themselves with the terrors
        of the darkness.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut they disappear like foam down a river.Everything they own
        is cursed,and they are afraid to enter their own vineyards.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The grave[[COMMENT(0)]] consumes sinnersjust as drought and heat
        consume snow.  '
      comments:
      - number: '24:19 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Sheol.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Their own mothers will forget them.Maggots will find them sweet to
        eat.No one will remember them.Wicked people are broken like a tree in the
        storm.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They cheat the woman who has no son to help her.They refuse to help
        the needy widow.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CGod, in his power, drags away the rich.They may rise high,
        but they have no assurance of life.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They may be allowed to live in security,but God is always watching
        them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And though they are great now,in a moment they will be gone like
        all others,cut off like heads of grain.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "Bildad\u2019s Third Response to Job"
      content: '  Then Bildad the Shuhite replied:  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CGod is powerful and dreadful.He enforces peace in the heavens.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Who is able to count his heavenly army?Doesn\u2019t his light shine
        on all the earth?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'How can a mortal be innocent before God?Can anyone born of a woman
        be pure?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'God is more glorious than the moon;he shines brighter than the stars.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "Job\u2019s Ninth Speech: A Response to Bildad"
      content: '  Then Job spoke again:  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CHow you have helped the powerless!How you have saved the weak!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'How you have enlightened my stupidity!What wise advice you have offered!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Where have you gotten all these wise sayings?Whose spirit speaks
        through you?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThe dead tremble\u2014those who live beneath the waters.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The underworld[[COMMENT(0)]] is naked in God\u2019s presence.The
        place of destruction[[COMMENT(1)]] is uncovered.  "
      comments:
      - number: '26:6a '
        content: Hebrew <b>Sheol.</b>
      - number: '26:6b '
        content: Hebrew <b>Abaddon.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'God stretches the northern sky over empty spaceand hangs the earth
        on nothing.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He wraps the rain in his thick clouds,and the clouds don\u2019t burst
        with the weight.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He covers the face of the moon,[[COMMENT(0)]]shrouding it with his
        clouds.  '
      comments:
      - number: '26:9 '
        content: Or <b>covers his throne.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'He created the horizon when he separated the waters;he set the boundary
        between day and night.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The foundations of heaven tremble;they shudder at his rebuke.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'By his power the sea grew calm.By his skill he crushed the great
        sea monster.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '26:12 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Rahab, </b>the name of a mythical sea monster that represents
          chaos in ancient literature.
    - title: 
      content: 'His Spirit made the heavens beautiful,and his power pierced the gliding
        serpent.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "Job\u2019s Final Speech"
      content: '  Job continued speaking:  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI vow by the living God, who has taken away my rights,by the
        Almighty who has embittered my soul\u2014  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'As long as I live,while I have breath from God,  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'my lips will speak no evil,and my tongue will speak no lies.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I will never concede that you are right;I will defend my integrity
        until I die.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I will maintain my innocence without wavering.My conscience is clear
        for as long as I live.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CMay my enemy be punished like the wicked,my adversary like
        those who do evil.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For what hope do the godless have when God cuts them offand takes
        away their life?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Will God listen to their crywhen trouble comes upon them?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Can they take delight in the Almighty?Can they call to God at any
        time?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will teach you about God\u2019s power.I will not conceal anything
        concerning the Almighty.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But you have seen all this,yet you say all these useless things to
        me.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThis is what the wicked will receive from God;this is their
        inheritance from the Almighty.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They may have many children,but the children will die in war or starve
        to death.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Those who survive will die of a plague,and not even their widows
        will mourn them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CEvil people may have piles of moneyand may store away mounds
        of clothing.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But the righteous will wear that clothing,and the innocent will divide
        that money.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The wicked build houses as fragile as a spider\u2019s web,[[COMMENT(0)]]as
        flimsy as a shelter made of branches.  "
      comments:
      - number: '27:18 '
        content: As in Greek and Syriac versions (see also 8:14); Hebrew reads <b>a
          moth.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'The wicked go to bed richbut wake to find that all their wealth is
        gone.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Terror overwhelms them like a flood,and they are blown away in the
        storms of the night.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The east wind carries them away, and they are gone.It sweeps them
        away.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'It whirls down on them without mercy.They struggle to flee from its
        power.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Job Speaks of Wisdom and Understanding
      content: "  \u201CPeople know where to mine silverand how to refine gold.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They know where to dig iron from the earthand how to smelt copper
        from rock.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They know how to shine light in the darknessand explore the farthest
        regions of the earthas they search in the dark for ore.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They sink a mine shaft into the earthfar from where anyone lives.They
        descend on ropes, swinging back and forth.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Food is grown on the earth above,but down below, the earth is melted
        as by fire.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Here the rocks contain precious lapis lazuli,and the dust contains
        gold.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "These are treasures no bird of prey can see,no falcon\u2019s eye
        observe.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'No wild animal has walked upon these treasures;no lion has ever set
        his paw there.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'People know how to tear apart flinty rocksand overturn the roots
        of mountains.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They cut tunnels in the rocksand uncover precious stones.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They dam up the trickling streamsand bring to light the hidden treasures.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut do people know where to find wisdom?Where can they find
        understanding?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'No one knows where to find it,[[COMMENT(0)]]for it is not found among
        the living.  '
      comments:
      - number: '28:13 '
        content: As in Greek version; Hebrew reads <b>knows its value.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "\u2018It is not here,\u2019 says the ocean.\u2018Nor is it here,\u2019
        says the sea.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'It cannot be bought with gold.It cannot be purchased with silver.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "It\u2019s worth more than all the gold of Ophir,greater than precious
        onyx or lapis lazuli.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Wisdom is more valuable than gold and crystal.It cannot be purchased
        with jewels mounted in fine gold.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Coral and jasper are worthless in trying to get it.The price of wisdom
        is far above rubies.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Precious peridot from Ethiopia[[COMMENT(0)]] cannot be exchanged
        for it.It\u2019s worth more than the purest gold.  "
      comments:
      - number: '28:19 '
        content: Hebrew <b>from Cush.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut do people know where to find wisdom?Where can they find
        understanding?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'It is hidden from the eyes of all humanity.Even the sharp-eyed birds
        in the sky cannot discover it.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Destruction[[COMMENT(0)]] and Death say,\u2018We\u2019ve heard only
        rumors of where wisdom can be found.\u2019  "
      comments:
      - number: '28:22 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Abaddon.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CGod alone understands the way to wisdom;he knows where it can
        be found,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'for he looks throughout the whole earthand sees everything under
        the heavens.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He decided how hard the winds should blowand how much rain should
        fall.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He made the laws for the rainand laid out a path for the lightning.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then he saw wisdom and evaluated it.He set it in place and examined
        it thoroughly.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Job Speaks of His Former Blessings
      content: '  Job continued speaking:  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI long for the years gone bywhen God took care of me,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'when he lit up the way before meand I walked safely through the darkness.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When I was in my prime,God\u2019s friendship was felt in my home.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The Almighty was still with me,and my children were around me.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'My steps were awash in cream,and the rocks gushed olive oil for me.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThose were the days when I went to the city gateand took my
        place among the honored leaders.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The young stepped aside when they saw me,and even the aged rose in
        respect at my coming.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The princes stood in silenceand put their hands over their mouths.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The highest officials of the city stood quietly,holding their tongues
        in respect.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CAll who heard me praised me.All who saw me spoke well of me.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For I assisted the poor in their needand the orphans who required
        help.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I helped those without hope, and they blessed me.And I caused the
        widows\u2019 hearts to sing for joy.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Everything I did was honest.Righteousness covered me like a robe,and
        I wore justice like a turban.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I served as eyes for the blindand feet for the lame.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I was a father to the poorand assisted strangers who needed help.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I broke the jaws of godless oppressorsand plucked their victims from
        their teeth.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI thought, \u2018Surely I will die surrounded by my familyafter
        a long, good life.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '29:18 '
        content: Hebrew <b>after I have counted my days like sand.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'For I am like a tree whose roots reach the water,whose branches are
        refreshed with the dew.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "New honors are constantly bestowed on me,and my strength is continually
        renewed.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CEveryone listened to my advice.They were silent as they waited
        for me to speak.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And after I spoke, they had nothing to add,for my counsel satisfied
        them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They longed for me to speak as people long for rain.They drank my
        words like a refreshing spring rain.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When they were discouraged, I smiled at them.My look of approval
        was precious to them.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Job Speaks of His Anguish
      content: "  \u201CBut now I am mocked by people younger than I,by young men
        whose fathers are not worthy to run with my sheepdogs.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "A lot of good they are to me\u2014those worn-out wretches!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They are gaunt from poverty and hunger.They claw the dry ground in
        desolate wastelands.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They pluck wild greens from among the bushesand eat from the roots
        of broom trees.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They are driven from human society,and people shout at them as if
        they were thieves.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So now they live in frightening ravines,in caves and among the rocks.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They sound like animals howling among the bushes,huddled together
        beneath the nettles.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They are nameless fools,outcasts from society.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CAnd now they mock me with vulgar songs!They taunt me!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They despise me and won\u2019t come near me,except to spit in my
        face.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For God has cut my bowstring.He has humbled me,so they have thrown
        off all restraint.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'These outcasts oppose me to my face.They send me sprawlingand lay
        traps in my path.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They block my roadand do everything they can to destroy me.They know
        I have no one to help me.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They come at me from all directions.They jump on me when I am down.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I live in terror now.My honor has blown away in the wind,and my prosperity
        has vanished like a cloud.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CAnd now my life seeps away.Depression haunts my days.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'At night my bones are filled with pain,which gnaws at me relentlessly.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'With a strong hand, God grabs my shirt.[[COMMENT(0)]]He grips me
        by the collar of my coat.  '
      comments:
      - number: '30:18 '
        content: As in Greek version; Hebrew reads <b>hand, my garment is disfigured.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "He has thrown me into the mud.I\u2019m nothing more than dust and
        ashes.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI cry to you, O God, but you don\u2019t answer.I stand before
        you, but you don\u2019t even look.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You have become cruel toward me.You use your power to persecute me.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You throw me into the whirlwindand destroy me in the storm.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And I know you are sending me to my death\u2014the destination of
        all who live.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CSurely no one would turn against the needywhen they cry for
        help in their trouble.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Did I not weep for those in trouble?Was I not deeply grieved for
        the needy?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So I looked for good, but evil came instead.I waited for the light,
        but darkness fell.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'My heart is troubled and restless.Days of suffering torment me.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I walk in gloom, without sunlight.I stand in the public square and
        cry for help.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Instead, I am considered a brother to jackalsand a companion to owls.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'My skin has turned dark,and my bones burn with fever.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "Job\u2019s Final Protest of Innocence"
      content: "  \u201CI made a covenant with my eyesnot to look with lust at a
        young woman.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For what has God above chosen for us?What is our inheritance from
        the Almighty on high?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Isn\u2019t it calamity for the wickedand misfortune for those who
        do evil?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Doesn\u2019t he see everything I doand every step I take?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CHave I lied to anyoneor deceived anyone?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Let God weigh me on the scales of justice,for he knows my integrity.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'If I have strayed from his pathway,or if my heart has lusted for
        what my eyes have seen,or if I am guilty of any other sin,  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'then let someone else eat the crops I have planted.Let all that I
        have planted be uprooted.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CIf my heart has been seduced by a woman,or if I have lusted
        for my neighbor\u2019s wife,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'then let my wife serve[[COMMENT(0)]] another man;let other men sleep
        with her.  '
      comments:
      - number: '31:10 '
        content: Hebrew <b>grind for.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'For lust is a shameful sin,a crime that should be punished.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'It is a fire that burns all the way to hell.[[COMMENT(0)]]It would
        wipe out everything I own.  '
      comments:
      - number: '31:12 '
        content: Hebrew <b>to Abaddon.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CIf I have been unfair to my male or female servantswhen they
        brought their complaints to me,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'how could I face God?What could I say when he questioned me?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For God created both me and my servants.He created us both in the
        womb.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CHave I refused to help the poor,or crushed the hopes of widows?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Have I been stingy with my foodand refused to share it with orphans?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'No, from childhood I have cared for orphans like a father,and all
        my life I have cared for widows.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Whenever I saw the homeless without clothesand the needy with nothing
        to wear,  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'did they not praise mefor providing wool clothing to keep them warm?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CIf I raised my hand against an orphan,knowing the judges would
        take my side,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'then let my shoulder be wrenched out of place!Let my arm be torn
        from its socket!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "That would be better than facing God\u2019s judgment.For if the majesty
        of God opposes me, what hope is there?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CHave I put my trust in moneyor felt secure because of my gold?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Have I gloated about my wealthand all that I own?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CHave I looked at the sun shining in the skies,or the moon walking
        down its silver pathway,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'and been secretly enticed in my heartto throw kisses at them in worship?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'If so, I should be punished by the judges,for it would mean I had
        denied the God of heaven.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CHave I ever rejoiced when disaster struck my enemies,or become
        excited when harm came their way?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'No, I have never sinned by cursing anyoneor by asking for revenge.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CMy servants have never said,\u2018He let others go hungry.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I have never turned away a strangerbut have opened my doors to everyone.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CHave I tried to hide my sins like other people do,concealing
        my guilt in my heart?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Have I feared the crowdor the contempt of the masses,so that I kept
        quiet and stayed indoors?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CIf only someone would listen to me!Look, I will sign my name
        to my defense.Let the Almighty answer me.Let my accuser write out the charges
        against me.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I would face the accusation proudly.I would wear it like a crown.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For I would tell him exactly what I have done.I would come before
        him like a prince.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CIf my land accuses meand all its furrows cry out together,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'or if I have stolen its cropsor murdered its owners,  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "Elihu Responds to Job\u2019s Friends"
      content: "  Job\u2019s three friends refused to reply further to him because
        he kept insisting on his innocence.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then Elihu son of Barakel the Buzite, of the clan of Ram, became
        angry. He was angry because Job refused to admit that he had sinned and that
        God was right in punishing him. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He was also angry with Job\u2019s three friends, for they made God[[COMMENT(0)]]
        appear to be wrong by their inability to answer Job\u2019s arguments. "
      comments:
      - number: '32:3 '
        content: As in ancient Hebrew scribal tradition; the Masoretic Text reads
          <b>Job.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Elihu had waited for the others to speak to Job because they were
        older than he. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But when he saw that they had no further reply, he spoke out angrily. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Elihu son of Barakel the Buzite said,\u201CI am young and you are
        old,so I held back from telling you what I think.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I thought, \u2018Those who are older should speak,for wisdom comes
        with age.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But there is a spirit[[COMMENT(0)]] within people,the breath of the
        Almighty within them,that makes them intelligent.  '
      comments:
      - number: '32:8 '
        content: Or <b>Spirit; </b>also in 32:18.
    - title: 
      content: 'Sometimes the elders are not wise.Sometimes the aged do not understand
        justice.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So listen to me,and let me tell you what I think.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI have waited all this time,listening very carefully to your
        arguments,listening to you grope for words.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I have listened,but not one of you has refuted Jobor answered his
        arguments.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And don\u2019t tell me, \u2018He is too wise for us.Only God can
        convince him.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'If Job had been arguing with me,I would not answer with your kind
        of logic!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You sit there baffled,with nothing more to say.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Should I continue to wait, now that you are silent?Must I also remain
        silent?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'No, I will say my piece.I will speak my mind.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For I am full of pent-up words,and the spirit within me urges me
        on.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I am like a cask of wine without a vent,like a new wineskin ready
        to burst!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I must speak to find relief,so let me give my answers.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I won\u2019t play favoritesor try to flatter anyone.  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Elihu Presents His Case against Job
      content: "  \u201CListen to my words, Job;pay attention to what I have to say.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Now that I have begun to speak,let me continue.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I speak with all sincerity;I speak the truth.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For the Spirit of God has made me,and the breath of the Almighty
        gives me life.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Answer me, if you can;make your case and take your stand.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Look, you and I both belong to God.I, too, was formed from clay.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So you don\u2019t need to be afraid of me.I won\u2019t come down
        hard on you.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CYou have spoken in my hearing,and I have heard your very words.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You said, \u2018I am pure; I am without sin;I am innocent; I have
        no guilt.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'God is picking a quarrel with me,and he considers me his enemy.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He puts my feet in the stocksand watches my every move.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut you are wrong, and I will show you why.For God is greater
        than any human being.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So why are you bringing a charge against him?Why say he does not
        respond to people\u2019s complaints?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For God speaks again and again,though people do not recognize it.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He speaks in dreams, in visions of the night,when deep sleep falls
        on peopleas they lie in their beds.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He whispers in their earsand terrifies them with warnings.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He makes them turn from doing wrong;he keeps them from pride.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He protects them from the grave,from crossing over the river of death.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201COr God disciplines people with pain on their sickbeds,with
        ceaseless aching in their bones.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They lose their appetitefor even the most delicious food.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Their flesh wastes away,and their bones stick out.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They are at death\u2019s door;the angels of death wait for them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut if an angel from heaven appears\u2014a special messenger
        to intercede for a personand declare that he is upright\u2014  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "he will be gracious and say,\u2018Rescue him from the grave,for I
        have found a ransom for his life.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then his body will become as healthy as a child\u2019s,firm and youthful
        again.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When he prays to God,he will be accepted.And God will receive him
        with joyand restore him to good standing.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He will declare to his friends,\u2018I sinned and twisted the truth,but
        it was not worth it.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '33:27 '
        content: Greek version reads <b>but he </b>[God] <b>did not punish me as
          my sin deserved.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "God rescued me from the grave,and now my life is filled with light.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CYes, God does these thingsagain and again for people.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He rescues them from the graveso they may enjoy the light of life.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Mark this well, Job. Listen to me,for I have more to say.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But if you have anything to say, go ahead.Speak, for I am anxious
        to see you justified.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Elihu Accuses Job of Arrogance
      content: '  Then Elihu said:  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CListen to me, you wise men.Pay attention, you who have knowledge.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Job said, \u2018The ear tests the words it hearsjust as the mouth
        distinguishes between foods.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So let us discern for ourselves what is right;let us learn together
        what is good.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For Job also said, \u2018I am innocent,but God has taken away my
        rights.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I am innocent, but they call me a liar.My suffering is incurable,
        though I have not sinned.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CTell me, has there ever been a man like Job,with his thirst
        for irreverent talk?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He chooses evil people as companions.He spends his time with wicked
        men.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He has even said, \u2018Why waste timetrying to please God?\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CListen to me, you who have understanding.Everyone knows that
        God doesn\u2019t sin!The Almighty can do no wrong.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He repays people according to their deeds.He treats people as they
        deserve.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Truly, God will not do wrong.The Almighty will not twist justice.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Did someone else put the world in his care?Who set the whole world
        in place?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'If God were to take back his spiritand withdraw his breath,  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'all life would cease,and humanity would turn again to dust.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CNow listen to me if you are wise.Pay attention to what I say.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Could God govern if he hated justice?Are you going to condemn the
        almighty judge?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For he says to kings, \u2018You are wicked,\u2019and to nobles, \u2018You
        are unjust.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He doesn\u2019t care how great a person may be,and he pays no more
        attention to the rich than to the poor.He made them all.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'In a moment they die.In the middle of the night they pass away;the
        mighty are removed without human hand.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CFor God watches how people live;he sees everything they do.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'No darkness is thick enoughto hide the wicked from his eyes.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "We don\u2019t set the timewhen we will come before God in judgment.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He brings the mighty to ruin without asking anyone,and he sets up
        others in their place.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He knows what they do,and in the night he overturns and destroys
        them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He strikes them down because they are wicked,doing it openly for
        all to see.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For they turned away from following him.They have no respect for
        any of his ways.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They cause the poor to cry out, catching God\u2019s attention.He
        hears the cries of the needy.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But if he chooses to remain quiet,who can criticize him?When he hides
        his face, no one can find him,whether an individual or a nation.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He prevents the godless from rulingso they cannot be a snare to the
        people.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWhy don\u2019t people say to God, \u2018I have sinned,but I
        will sin no more\u2019?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Or \u2018I don\u2019t know what evil I have done\u2014tell me.If
        I have done wrong, I will stop at once\u2019?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CMust God tailor his justice to your demands?But you have rejected
        him!The choice is yours, not mine.Go ahead, share your wisdom with us.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'After all, bright people will tell me,and wise people will hear me
        say,  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u2018Job speaks out of ignorance;his words lack insight.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Job, you deserve the maximum penaltyfor the wicked way you have talked.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "Elihu Reminds Job of God\u2019s Justice"
      content: '  Then Elihu said:  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CDo you think it is right for you to claim,\u2018I am righteous
        before God\u2019?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For you also ask, \u2018What\u2019s in it for me?What\u2019s the
        use of living a righteous life?\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI will answer youand all your friends, too.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Look up into the sky,and see the clouds high above you.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'If you sin, how does that affect God?Even if you sin again and again,what
        effect will it have on him?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'If you are good, is this some great gift to him?What could you possibly
        give him?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'No, your sins affect only people like yourself,and your good deeds
        also affect only humans.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CPeople cry out when they are oppressed.They groan beneath the
        power of the mighty.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Yet they don\u2019t ask, \u2018Where is God my Creator,the one who
        gives songs in the night?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Where is the one who makes us smarter than the animalsand wiser than
        the birds of the sky?\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And when they cry out, God does not answerbecause of their pride.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But it is wrong to say God doesn\u2019t listen,to say the Almighty
        isn\u2019t concerned.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You say you can\u2019t see him,but he will bring justice if you will
        only wait.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '35:13-14 '
        content: "These verses can also be translated as follows: <b>Indeed, God
          doesn\u2019t listen to their empty plea; / the Almighty is not concerned.
          / </b><b>How much less will he listen when you say you don\u2019t see him,
          / and that your case is before him and you\u2019re waiting for justice.</b>"
    - title: 
      content: 'You say he does not respond to sinners with angerand is not greatly
        concerned about wickedness.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '35:15 '
        content: As in Greek and Latin versions; the meaning of this Hebrew word
          is uncertain.
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: '  Elihu continued speaking:  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CLet me go on, and I will show you the truth.For I have not
        finished defending God!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I will present profound argumentsfor the righteousness of my Creator.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I am telling you nothing but the truth,for I am a man of great knowledge.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CGod is mighty, but he does not despise anyone!He is mighty
        in both power and understanding.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He does not let the wicked livebut gives justice to the afflicted.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He never takes his eyes off the innocent,but he sets them on thrones
        with kingsand exalts them forever.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'If they are bound in chainsand caught up in a web of trouble,  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'he shows them the reason.He shows them their sins of pride.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He gets their attentionand commands that they turn from evil.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CIf they listen and obey God,they will be blessed with prosperity
        throughout their lives.All their years will be pleasant.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But if they refuse to listen to him,they will cross over the river
        of death,dying from lack of understanding.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For the godless are full of resentment.Even when he punishes them,they
        refuse to cry out to him for help.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They die when they are young,after wasting their lives in immoral
        living.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But by means of their suffering, he rescues those who suffer.For
        he gets their attention through adversity.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CGod is leading you away from danger, Job,to a place free from
        distress.He is setting your table with the best food.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But you are obsessed with whether the godless will be judged.Don\u2019t
        worry, judgment and justice will be upheld.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But watch out, or you may be seduced by wealth.[[COMMENT(0)]]Don\u2019t
        let yourself be bribed into sin.  "
      comments:
      - number: '36:18 '
        content: "Or <b>But don\u2019t let your anger lead you to mockery.</b>"
    - title: 
      content: 'Could all your wealth[[COMMENT(0)]]or all your mighty effortskeep
        you from distress?  '
      comments:
      - number: '36:19 '
        content: Or <b>Could all your cries for help.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Do not long for the cover of night,for that is when people will be
        destroyed.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '36:16-20 '
        content: The meaning of the Hebrew in this passage is uncertain.
    - title: "Elihu Reminds Job of God\u2019s Power"
      content: 'Be on guard! Turn back from evil,for God sent this sufferingto keep
        you from a life of evil.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CLook, God is all-powerful.Who is a teacher like him?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "No one can tell him what to do,or say to him, \u2018You have done
        wrong.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Instead, glorify his mighty works,singing songs of praise.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Everyone has seen these things,though only from a distance.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CLook, God is greater than we can understand.His years cannot
        be counted.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He draws up the water vaporand then distills it into rain.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The rain pours down from the clouds,and everyone benefits.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Who can understand the spreading of the cloudsand the thunder that
        rolls forth from heaven?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'See how he spreads the lightning around himand how it lights up the
        depths of the sea.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'By these mighty acts he nourishes[[COMMENT(0)]] the people,giving
        them food in abundance.  '
      comments:
      - number: '36:31 '
        content: Or <b>he governs.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'He fills his hands with lightning boltsand hurls each at its target.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CMy heart pounds as I think of this.It trembles within me.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Listen carefully to the thunder of God\u2019s voiceas it rolls from
        his mouth.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'It rolls across the heavens,and his lightning flashes in every direction.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then comes the roaring of the thunder\u2014the tremendous voice of
        his majesty.He does not restrain it when he speaks.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "God\u2019s voice is glorious in the thunder.We can\u2019t even imagine
        the greatness of his power.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CHe directs the snow to fall on the earthand tells the rain
        to pour down.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then everyone stops workingso they can watch his power.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The wild animals take coverand stay inside their dens.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The stormy wind comes from its chamber,and the driving winds bring
        the cold.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "God\u2019s breath sends the ice,freezing wide expanses of water.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He loads the clouds with moisture,and they flash with his lightning.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The clouds churn about at his direction.They do whatever he commands
        throughout the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He makes these things happen either to punish peopleor to show his
        unfailing love.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CPay attention to this, Job.Stop and consider the wonderful
        miracles of God!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Do you know how God controls the stormand causes the lightning to
        flash from his clouds?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Do you understand how he moves the cloudswith wonderful perfection
        and skill?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When you are sweltering in your clothesand the south wind dies down
        and everything is still,  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'he makes the skies reflect the heat like a bronze mirror.Can you
        do that?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CSo teach the rest of us what to say to God.We are too ignorant
        to make our own arguments.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Should God be notified that I want to speak?Can people even speak
        when they are confused?[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '37:20 '
        content: Or <b>speak without being swallowed up?</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'We cannot look at the sun,for it shines brightly in the skywhen the
        wind clears away the clouds.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So also, golden splendor comes from the mountain of God.[[COMMENT(0)]]He
        is clothed in dazzling splendor.  '
      comments:
      - number: '37:22 '
        content: Or <b>from the north; </b>or <b>from the abode.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'We cannot imagine the power of the Almighty;but even though he is
        just and righteous,he does not destroy us.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> Challenges Job
      content: '  Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> answered Job from the whirlwind:  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWho is this that questions my wisdomwith such ignorant words?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Brace yourself like a man,because I have some questions for you,and
        you must answer them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWhere were you when I laid the foundations of the earth?Tell
        me, if you know so much.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Who determined its dimensionsand stretched out the surveying line?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'What supports its foundations,and who laid its cornerstone  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'as the morning stars sang togetherand all the angels[[COMMENT(0)]]
        shouted for joy?  '
      comments:
      - number: '38:7 '
        content: Hebrew <b>the sons of God.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWho kept the sea inside its boundariesas it burst from the
        womb,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'and as I clothed it with cloudsand wrapped it in thick darkness?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For I locked it behind barred gates,limiting its shores.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I said, \u2018This far and no farther will you come.Here your proud
        waves must stop!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CHave you ever commanded the morning to appearand caused the
        dawn to rise in the east?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Have you made daylight spread to the ends of the earth,to bring an
        end to the night\u2019s wickedness?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'As the light approaches,the earth takes shape like clay pressed beneath
        a seal;it is robed in brilliant colors.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '38:14 '
        content: Or <b>its features stand out like folds in a robe.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'The light disturbs the wickedand stops the arm that is raised in
        violence.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CHave you explored the springs from which the seas come?Have
        you explored their depths?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Do you know where the gates of death are located?Have you seen the
        gates of utter gloom?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Do you realize the extent of the earth?Tell me about it if you know!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWhere does light come from,and where does darkness go?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Can you take each to its home?Do you know how to get there?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But of course you know all this!For you were born before it was all
        created,and you are so very experienced!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CHave you visited the storehouses of the snowor seen the storehouses
        of hail?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: '(I have reserved them as weapons for the time of trouble,for the
        day of battle and war.)  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Where is the path to the source of light?Where is the home of the
        east wind?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWho created a channel for the torrents of rain?Who laid out
        the path for the lightning?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Who makes the rain fall on barren land,in a desert where no one lives?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Who sends rain to satisfy the parched groundand make the tender grass
        spring up?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CDoes the rain have a father?Who gives birth to the dew?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Who is the mother of the ice?Who gives birth to the frost from the
        heavens?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For the water turns to ice as hard as rock,and the surface of the
        water freezes.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CCan you direct the movement of the stars\u2014binding the cluster
        of the Pleiadesor loosening the cords of Orion?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Can you direct the constellations through the seasonsor guide the
        Bear with her cubs across the heavens?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Do you know the laws of the universe?Can you use them to regulate
        the earth?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CCan you shout to the cloudsand make it rain?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Can you make lightning appearand cause it to strike as you direct?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Who gives intuition to the heartand instinct to the mind?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Who is wise enough to count all the clouds?Who can tilt the water
        jars of heaven  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'when the parched ground is dryand the soil has hardened into clods?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CCan you stalk prey for a lionessand satisfy the young lions\u2019
        appetites  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'as they lie in their densor crouch in the thicket?  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s Challenge Continues"
      content: "  \u201CDo you know when the wild goats give birth?Have you watched
        as deer are born in the wild?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Do you know how many months they carry their young?Are you aware
        of the time of their delivery?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They crouch down to give birth to their youngand deliver their offspring.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Their young grow up in the open fields,then leave home and never
        return.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWho gives the wild donkey its freedom?Who untied its ropes?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I have placed it in the wilderness;its home is the wasteland.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'It hates the noise of the cityand has no driver to shout at it.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The mountains are its pastureland,where it searches for every blade
        of grass.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWill the wild ox consent to being tamed?Will it spend the night
        in your stall?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Can you hitch a wild ox to a plow?Will it plow a field for you?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Given its strength, can you trust it?Can you leave and trust the
        ox to do your work?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Can you rely on it to bring home your grainand deliver it to your
        threshing floor?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThe ostrich flaps her wings grandly,but they are no match for
        the feathers of the stork.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'She lays her eggs on top of the earth,letting them be warmed in the
        dust.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "She doesn\u2019t worry that a foot might crush themor a wild animal
        might destroy them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "She is harsh toward her young,as if they were not her own.She doesn\u2019t
        care if they die.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For God has deprived her of wisdom.He has given her no understanding.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But whenever she jumps up to run,she passes the swiftest horse with
        its rider.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CHave you given the horse its strengthor clothed its neck with
        a flowing mane?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Did you give it the ability to leap like a locust?Its majestic snorting
        is terrifying!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'It paws the earth and rejoices in its strengthwhen it charges out
        to battle.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'It laughs at fear and is unafraid.It does not run from the sword.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The arrows rattle against it,and the spear and javelin flash.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "It paws the ground fiercelyand rushes forward into battle when the
        ram\u2019s horn blows.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "It snorts at the sound of the horn.It senses the battle in the distance.It
        quivers at the captain\u2019s commands and the noise of battle.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CIs it your wisdom that makes the hawk soarand spread its wings
        toward the south?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Is it at your command that the eagle risesto the heights to make
        its nest?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'It lives on the cliffs,making its home on a distant, rocky crag.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'From there it hunts its prey,keeping watch with piercing eyes.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: '  Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Job,  '
      comments: []
    - title: Job Responds to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
      content: "\u201CDo you still want to argue with the Almighty?You are God\u2019s
        critic, but do you have the answers?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then Job replied to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI am nothing\u2014how could I ever find the answers?I will
        cover my mouth with my hand.  "
      comments: []
    - title: The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> Challenges Job Again
      content: "I have said too much already.I have nothing more to say.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> answered Job from the whirlwind:  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBrace yourself like a man,because I have some questions for
        you,and you must answer them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWill you discredit my justiceand condemn me just to prove you
        are right?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Are you as strong as God?Can you thunder with a voice like his?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'All right, put on your glory and splendor,your honor and majesty.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Give vent to your anger.Let it overflow against the proud.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Humiliate the proud with a glance;walk on the wicked where they stand.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Bury them in the dust.Imprison them in the world of the dead.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then even I would praise you,for your own strength would save you.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CTake a look at Behemoth,[[COMMENT(0)]]which I made, just as
        I made you.It eats grass like an ox.  "
      comments:
      - number: '40:15 '
        content: The identification of Behemoth is disputed, ranging from an earthly
          creature to a mythical sea monster in ancient literature.
    - title: 
      content: 'See its powerful loinsand the muscles of its belly.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Its tail is as strong as a cedar.The sinews of its thighs are knit
        tightly together.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Its bones are tubes of bronze.Its limbs are bars of iron.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "It is a prime example of God\u2019s handiwork,and only its Creator
        can threaten it.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The mountains offer it their best food,where all the wild animals
        play.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'It lies under the lotus plants,[[COMMENT(0)]]hidden by the reeds
        in the marsh.  '
      comments:
      - number: '40:21 '
        content: Or <b>bramble bushes; </b>also in 40:22.
    - title: 
      content: 'The lotus plants give it shadeamong the willows beside the stream.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'It is not disturbed by the raging river,not concerned when the swelling
        Jordan rushes around it.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s Challenge Continues"
      content: "    [[COMMENT(0)]]\u201CCan you catch Leviathan[[COMMENT(1)]] with
        a hookor put a noose around its jaw?  "
      comments:
      - number: '41:1a '
        content: '  Verses 41:1-8 are numbered 40:25-32 in Hebrew text.  '
      - number: '41:1b '
        content: 'The identification of Leviathan is disputed, ranging from an earthly
          creature to a mythical sea monster in ancient literature.  '
    - title: 
      content: 'Can you tie it with a rope through the noseor pierce its jaw with
        a spike?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Will it beg you for mercyor implore you for pity?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Will it agree to work for you,to be your slave for life?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Can you make it a pet like a bird,or give it to your little girls
        to play with?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Will merchants try to buy itto sell it in their shops?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Will its hide be hurt by spearsor its head by a harpoon?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "If you lay a hand on it,you will certainly remember the battle that
        follows.You won\u2019t try that again!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: '  [[COMMENT(0)]]No, it is useless to try to capture it.The hunter
        who attempts it will be knocked down.  '
      comments:
      - number: '41:9 '
        content: '  Verses 41:9-34 are numbered 41:1-26 in Hebrew text.  '
    - title: 
      content: 'And since no one dares to disturb it,who then can stand up to me?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Who has given me anything that I need to pay back?Everything under
        heaven is mine.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI want to emphasize Leviathan\u2019s limbsand its enormous
        strength and graceful form.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Who can strip off its hide,and who can penetrate its double layer
        of armor?[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '41:13 '
        content: As in Greek version; Hebrew reads <b>its bridle?</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Who could pry open its jaws?For its teeth are terrible!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The scales on its back are like[[COMMENT(0)]] rows of shieldstightly
        sealed together.  '
      comments:
      - number: '41:15 '
        content: As in some Greek manuscripts and Latin Vulgate; Hebrew reads <b>Its
          pride is in its.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'They are so close togetherthat no air can get between them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Each scale sticks tight to the next.They interlock and cannot be
        penetrated.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWhen it sneezes, it flashes light!Its eyes are like the red
        of dawn.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Lightning leaps from its mouth;flames of fire flash out.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Smoke streams from its nostrilslike steam from a pot heated over
        burning rushes.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Its breath would kindle coals,for flames shoot from its mouth.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThe tremendous strength in Leviathan\u2019s neckstrikes terror
        wherever it goes.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Its flesh is hard and firmand cannot be penetrated.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Its heart is hard as rock,hard as a millstone.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When it rises, the mighty are afraid,gripped by terror.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'No sword can stop it,no spear, dart, or javelin.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Iron is nothing but straw to that creature,and bronze is like rotten
        wood.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Arrows cannot make it flee.Stones shot from a sling are like bits
        of grass.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Clubs are like a blade of grass,and it laughs at the swish of javelins.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Its belly is covered with scales as sharp as glass.It plows up the
        ground as it drags through the mud.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CLeviathan makes the water boil with its commotion.It stirs
        the depths like a pot of ointment.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The water glistens in its wake,making the sea look white.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Nothing on earth is its equal,no other creature so fearless.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Job Responds to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
      content: '  Then Job replied to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>:  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI know that you can do anything,and no one can stop you.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You asked, \u2018Who is this that questions my wisdom with such ignorance?\u2019It
        is I\u2014and I was talking about things I knew nothing about,things far
        too wonderful for me.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You said, \u2018Listen and I will speak!I have some questions for
        you,and you must answer them.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I had only heard about you before,but now I have seen you with my
        own eyes.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 'Conclusion: The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> Blesses Job'
      content: "I take back everything I said,and I sit in dust and ashes to show
        my repentance.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "After the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> had finished speaking to Job,
        he said to Eliphaz the Temanite: \u201CI am angry with you and your two friends,
        for you have not spoken accurately about me, as my servant Job has. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So take seven bulls and seven rams and go to my servant Job and offer
        a burnt offering for yourselves. My servant Job will pray for you, and I
        will accept his prayer on your behalf. I will not treat you as you deserve,
        for you have not spoken accurately about me, as my servant Job has.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So Eliphaz the Temanite, Bildad the Shuhite, and Zophar the Naamathite
        did as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> commanded them, and the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        accepted Job\u2019s prayer.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When Job prayed for his friends, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        restored his fortunes. In fact, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave him
        twice as much as before! '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then all his brothers, sisters, and former friends came and feasted
        with him in his home. And they consoled him and comforted him because of
        all the trials the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> had brought against him. And
        each of them brought him a gift of money[[COMMENT(0)]] and a gold ring.  '
      comments:
      - number: '42:11 '
        content: Hebrew <b>a kesitah; </b>the value or weight of the kesitah is no
          longer known.
    - title: 
      content: 'So the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> blessed Job in the second half
        of his life even more than in the beginning. For now he had 14,000 sheep,
        6,000 camels, 1,000 teams of oxen, and 1,000 female donkeys. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He also gave Job seven more sons and three more daughters. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He named his first daughter Jemimah, the second Keziah, and the third
        Keren-happuch. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'In all the land no women were as lovely as the daughters of Job.
        And their father put them into his will along with their brothers.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Job lived 140 years after that, living to see four generations of
        his children and grandchildren. '
      comments: []
